Technical Implementation Steps
1. Data Acquisition and Preprocessing
Imported a real-world, highly detailed football dataset (EA Sports FC 26 player data) via a CSV file using Python and the Pandas library.
Cleaned and standardized the dataset by converting column names to lowercase and replacing spaces with underscores to prevent coding errors.
Filtered the dataset to isolate the target demographic: young prospects aged 21 and under.
2. Feature Selection and Target Definition
Isolated key physical, technical, and mental attributes relevant to a player's development: Age, Vision, Sprint Speed, Ball Control, Stamina, and Composure.
Defined the "Target Variable" for the algorithm: A player is classified as a future "Top Player" if their historical estimated potential is 85 or higher (Champions League level).
3. Machine Learning Model Training
Implemented an XGBoost Classifier, an industry-standard Machine Learning algorithm known for its high performance and accuracy with structured, tabular data.
Split the dataset into a training set (80% of the data to teach the algorithm) and a testing set (20% of the data to evaluate its performance).
Successfully trained the model, achieving an accuracy rate of over 98% on unseen data.
4. Explainable AI (XAI) Integration
Integrated the SHAP (SHapley Additive exPlanations) library to solve the "black box" problem typical of AI models.
Engineered the system to generate human-readable scouting reports. Instead of just providing a raw percentage, the system explains why a player was selected or rejected, detailing exactly how much each specific attribute (e.g., poor stamina or excellent vision) positively or negatively impacted the final prediction.
5. Automated Discovery and Data Visualization (Dashboard)
Scaled the algorithm to automatically calculate the success probability for the entire database of Under-21 players simultaneously.
Developed a ranking system to automatically extract a Top 20 Leaderboard of the highest-rated hidden talents.
Utilized Matplotlib and Seaborn libraries to generate a clean, professional horizontal bar chart, effectively transforming complex predictive data into an intuitive visual dashboard ready for sports directors and scouting departments.

